==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
French, 'stroke of grace'. Originally referring to a merciful stroke putting a fatally wounded person out of misery or to the shot delivered to the head of a prisoner after facing a firing squad.

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]]:/ku də gras/, /ku də ɡʁas/

===Noun===
'''coup de grâce''' (''Plural'' '''coups de grâce''')

# A final [[blow]] or [[shot]] given to [[kill]] a wounded person or animal.

[[Category:English words spelled with diacritics or ligatures|Coup de grace]]

